<item>
            <title>[RAT-109] Return value of mkdirs() is not checked and no error handling occurs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/RAT-109</link>
                <project id="12310750" key="RAT">Apache RAT</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The code contains calls to mkdir() without checking its return value.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch attached for classes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;apache-rat-plugin/src/main/java/org/apache/rat/mp/RatReportMojo.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;apache-rat-plugin/src/main/java/org/apache/rat/mp/RatCheckMojo.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;apache-rat-tasks/src/test/java/org/apache/rat/anttasks/ReportTest.java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
